column2: The Roman Administration manages and rules the Empire of the Romans
The Emperor is the leader of the administration of the Empire
Administrative Clientelism is a form a succession that favors members of a clientele or family members.
After the death of my [Root.GetFatherMother] and as I am now of age, it is time for me to pledge homage to my lord as my ancestors did before me.
I will travel to [Suzerain.capital_scope.GetName] to give my suzerain homage !
On second thought, let me reconsider this.
A messenger just arrived and informed me that [From.GetTitledName] is going to come in [Root.Capital_scope.GetName] to swear me homage.
We must receive him as befitting his rank with a lavish ceremony…
We must prepare for the upcoming ceremony.
Accept his homage quickly and without spending too much.
I do not want any entanglement with [From.GetTitledName] !
I just received a messenger from [From.GetTitledName] that he refuses to accept my homage ! This is an outrage !

Today, in front of many witnesses I brought myself to my knees before [From.GetTitledName] in sign of humility and swore upon a holy relic my oath of fidelity while he held my hands. As [From.GetTitledName] accepted my pledge, I rose, we made the kiss of peace and I received a symbolic token of my fealty. \n I am now [From.GetTitledName]'s man.
It was a nice ceremony and I was richly entertained.
What a stingy ceremony, it was unbefitting of my rank.

Today, in front of many witnesses [FromFrom.GetTitleName] brought himself to his knees before me in sign of humility and swore upon a holy relic his oath of fidelity while I held his hands. As I accepted his pledge, he rose, we made the kiss of peace and I gave him a symbolic token of his fealty.
He is now truly my vassal.
As is customary I should organize the royal plaid.
Donated lavishly for  my daughter's marriage
Donated meagre sum for my daughter's marriage
Donated nothing for my daughter's marriage
Donated meagre sum for the ransom
Donated meagre sum for the Crusade
